 = \u9ea5\u7530 | date = 2000-04-29| ISBN = 9574690210 | accessdate = 2020-04-06 | url = https://www.books.com.tw/products/0010008912 | language = Traditional Chinese }} </ref>\n* ''Inter-Frames: Word-Image-Music and the Semiotic Boundaries.'' Ed. Joyce Chi-Hui Liu. Taipei: Lixu Publisher. 1999. <ref> {{Cite book | author = \u5289\u7d00\u8559 | title = \u6846\u67b6\u5167\u5916\uff1a\u85dd\u8853\u3001\u6587\u985e\u8207\u7b26\u865f\u7586\u754c | publisher = \u7acb\u7dd2 | date = 1999-12-15 | ISBN = 9578453817 | accessdate = 2020-04-06 | url = https://www.books.com.tw/products/0010098677 | language = Traditional Chinese }} </ref>\n\n==Scholarly Translations into Chinese==\n* ''La M\u00e9sentente. Politique et philosophie. by Jacque Ranci\u00e8re.'' co-translated with Shufen Lin, Kelun Chen, Xiping Xue. Taipei: Maitian Publisher. 2011. <ref> {{Cite book | author = \u5289\u7d00\u8559\u3001\u6797\u6dd1\u82ac\u3001\u859b\u7199\u5e73\u3001\u9673\u514b\u502b | title = \u6b67\u7fa9\uff1a\u653f\u6cbb\u8207\u54f2\u5b78 | location = Taipei | publisher = \u9ea5\u7530 | date = 2011-04-19  | ISBN = 9789861735771 | accessdate = 2020-04-06 | url = http://www.eslite.com/product.aspx?pgid=1001156502021851 | language = Traditional Chinese }} </ref>\n* ''An Introductory Dictionary of Lacanian Psychoanalysis by Dylan Evans.'' co-translated with Chaoyang Liao, Zonghui Huang, Zhuojun Gong. Taipei: Juliu Publisher. 2009. <ref> {{Cite book | author = \u5289\u7d00\u8559\u3001\u5ed6\u671d\u967d\u3001\u9ec3\u5b97\u6167\u3001\u9f94\u5353\u8ecd | title = \u62c9\u5ca1\u7cbe\u795e\u5206\u6790\u8fad\u5f59 | location = Taipei | publisher = \u5de8\u6d41 | date = 2009-10-01 | ISBN = 9789577323361 | accessdate = 2020-04-06 | url = https://www.sanmin.com.tw/product/index/001017629 | language = Traditional Chinese }} </ref>\n* ''Milky Way.'' by Kaja Silverman. chungwai wenxue. 30.12 (2002.5): 25-53.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official website|http://www.srcs.nctu.edu.tw/joyceliu/}} ''In Chinese''\n*{{cite web | title=Joyce C.H. Liu | publisher= Graduate Institute for Social Research and Cultural Studies, NCTU| url=http://www.srcs.nctu.edu.tw/srcs_en/teachers_cv_01_e.htm}}\n*{{cite web|last=Liu|first=Joyce|title=The Graduate Institute for Social Research and Cultural Studies|url=http://www.srcs.nctu.edu.tw/srcs_en/intro.aspx|work=Professor|publisher=National Chiao Tung University|accessdate=2013-07-26}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://140.113.199.26/zh_tw/people/research_0/bygroup|title=Inter Asia Cultural Study Faculty Page|last=Liu|first=Joyce|publisher=Inter Asia Cultural Study|work=Professor|accessdate=2017-03-16}}\n\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Liu, Joyce C. H.}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:National Chiao Tung University faculty]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Fu Jen Catholic University alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Illinois at Urbana\u2013Champaign alumni]]\n[[Category:Taiwanese women academics]]\n[[Category:20th-century Taiwanese women writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Taiwanese women writers]]\n", "text_old": "{{multiple issues|\n{{autobiography|date=September 2018}}\n{{COI|date=September 2018}}\n{{more footnotes|date=October 2018}}\n}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name = Joyce C. H. Liu\n| native_name = \u5289\u7d00\u8559\n| native_name_lang = zh\n| width = \n| image = http://www.srcs.nctu.edu.tw/srcs/images_p02/teachers_cv/t01_photo_02.jpg\n| office1 = Director, International Center for Cultural Studies\n| office2 = Director, International Graduate Institute for Inter-Asia Cultural Studies, UST\n| office3 = Chair Professor, Institute of Social Research and Cultural Studies, National Chiao Tung University\n| period = \n| nationality = \n| education = [[University of Illinois]] (Ph.D.)\n| past = \n}}\n'''Joyce Chi-Hui Liu''' ({{zh|\u5289\u7d00\u8559}}[[:tw:\u5289\u7d00\u8559|)]]  is Professor of Critical Theory, Cultural Studies and Comparative Literature at [[National Chiao Tung University]], [[Taiwan]]. Liu is the Chair of the Institute of Social Research and Cultural Studies that she founded in 2002. She is also the director of the International Center for Cultural Studies of the [[University System of Taiwan]].<ref name=cv>{{citation|url=http://www.srcs.nctu.edu.tw/joyceliu/mworks/English%20CV.htm|title=Curriculum vitae|publisher=[[National Chiao Tung University]]|accessdate=2018-10-09}}</ref>\n\n== Education ==\nLiu obtained a bachelor's degree in English literature in 1978 from [[Fu Jen Catholic University]].\nShe moved to the [[University of Illinois at Urbana\u2013Champaign]] for graduate study in [[comparative literature]], earning a master's degree in 1980 and a Ph.D. in 1984.{{r|cv}}\n\n== Career ==\nLiu's works concentrate on the question of aesthetics, ethics, and politics, ranging from [[Karl Marx|Marx]], [[Sigmund Freud|Freud]] and [[Jacques Lacan|Lacan]], to contemporary critical theories as well as Chinese political thoughts. She has been a critic of East-Asian modernity and internal coloniality, particularly through re-reading the [[Chinese intellectualism|Chinese intellectual history]] of the twentieth century and the contemporary political-economy in inter-Asian societies.  She served as the chief editor of the only journal of [[cultural studies]] in Taiwan, ''Router: A Journal of Cultural Studies'', from 2012-2107.<ref name=nctu-profile>{{cite web | title=Joyce C.H. Liu | publisher= Graduate Institute for Social Research and Cultural Studies, NCTU| url=http://www.srcs.nctu.edu.tw/srcs_en/teachers_cv_01_e.htm | access-date=10 October 2018}}</ref> She is currently the Chair of the Institute of Social Research and Cultural Studies that she founded in 2002.<ref name=nctu-profile /> She is also the director of the International Center for Cultural Studies of the [[University System of Taiwan]].<ref name=nctu-profile />\n\n== Academic Positions ==\n2019-Present Chair Professor, Institute of Social Research and Cultural Studies (SRCS-NCTU), National Chiao Tung University, Hsinchu, Taiwan\n2012-Present Director, International Institute for Cultural Studies (IICS-NCTU & UST), National Chiao Tung University & University System of Taiwan\n2013-Present Director, International Graduate Institute for Inter-Asia Cultural Studies, University System of Taiwan\n2002-2019 Professor, Institute of Social Research and Cultural Studies (SRCS-NCTU), National Chiao Tung University, Hsinchu, Taiwan\n2013-2019 Director, Institute of Social Research and Cultural Studies, National Chiao Tung University, Hsinchu, Taiwan\n2011-2017 Chief Editor, Wenhua Yanjiu (Router: A Journal of Cultural Studies) \n2008-2011 Director, Institute of Social Research and Cultural Studies, National Chiao Tung University, Hsinchu, Taiwan\n2001-2006 Director, Center for Emergent Cultural Studies, National Chiao Tung University, Hsinchu, Taiwan     \n2002-2004 Director, Institute of Social Research and Cultural Studies, National Chiao Tung University, Hsinchu, Taiwan (Founding Director)\n2001-2002 Professor, Department of Foreign Languages and Literatures, National Chiao Tung University, Hsinchu, Taiwan\n2000-2002 President, Cultural Studies Association in Taiwan\n1994-2001 Professor, Graduate Institute of Comparative Literature, Fu Jen Catholic University\n1994-1999 Director, Graduate Institute of Comparative Literature, Fu Jen Catholic University, Taipei, Taiwan (Founding Director)\n1988-1993 Chair, English Department, Fu Jen Catholic University, Taipei, Taiwan\n1984-1994 Associate Professor, English Department, Fu Jen Catholic University, Taipei, Taiwan {{r|cv}}\n\n==Selected publications==\nAmong her publications, the representative works are the three co-edited volumes: ''East-Asian Marxisms and their Trajectories'' (Routledge 2017), ''European-East Asian Borders in Translation'' (Routledge 2014), ''Biopolitics, Ethics and Subjectivation'' (Paris: L'Harmattan, 2011) ;and the influential trilogy that she authored: ''The Topology of Psyche: The Post-1895 Reconfiguration of Ethics ''(2011), ''The Perverted Heart: The Psychic Forms of Modernity'' (2004), as well as ''Orphan, Goddess, and the Writing of the Negative: The Performance of Our Symptoms'' (2000).{{r|cv}}\n\n===Books===\n* ''One Divides into Two: Philosophical Archaeology of Modern Chinese Political Thought.'' Taipei: Lianjing Publisher, 2020. 462 ps. <ref> {{Cite book | author = \u5289\u7d00\u8559 | title = \u4e00\u5206\u70ba\u4e8c\uff1a\u73fe\u4ee3\u4e2d\u570b\u653f\u6cbb\u601d\u60f3\u7684\u54f2\u5b78\u8003\u6398\u5b78 | ISBN = 9789570854763 | accessdate = 2020-03-30 | url = https://www.books.com.tw/products/0010852839?sloc=main | language = Traditional Chinese }} </ref>\n* ''The Topology of Psyche: The Post-1895 Reconstruction of Ethics.'' Taipei: Flaneur, 2011. 446 ps. (NSC Publication Award 2011) <ref> {{Cite book | author = \u5289\u7d00\u8559 | title = \u5fc3\u4e4b\u62d3\u6a38\uff1a1895\u4e8b\u4ef6\u5f8c\u7684\u502b\u7406\u91cd\u69cb | ISBN = 9789868581074 | accessdate = 2020-03-30 | url = https://www.books.com.tw/products/0010499358 | language = Traditional Chinese }} </ref>\n* ''The Perverted Heart: The Psychic Forms of Modernity''. Taipei: Ryefield Publisher, 2004. 368ps. (NICT Publication Award 2004) <ref> {{Cite book | author = \u5289\u7d00\u8559 | title = \u5fc3\u7684\u8b8a\u7570\uff1a\u73fe\u4ee3\u6027\u7684\u7cbe\u795e\u5f62\u5f0f | ISBN = 9867413059 | accessdate = 2020-03-30 | url = https://www.books.com.tw/products/0010270357 | language = Traditional Chinese }} </ref>\n* ''Literature and Film: Image, Reality and Cultural Criticism''. Taipei. 161 ps. (Publication sponsored by NSC) <ref> {{Cite book | author = \u5289\u7d00\u8559 | title = \u6587\u5b78\u8207\u96fb\u5f71 : \u5f71\u50cf.\u771f\u5be6.\u6587\u5316\u6279\u8a55 | ISBN = 9576719410 | accessdate = 2020-03-30 | url = https://ir.nctu.edu.tw/handle/11536/106631 | language = Traditional Chinese  }} </ref>\n* ''Orphan, Goddess, and the Writing of the Negative: The Performance of Our Symptoms.'' Taipei: Lixu Publisher, 2000. 470ps. <ref> {{Cite book | author = \u5289\u7d00\u8559 | title = \u5b64\u5152\uff0e\u5973\u795e\uff0e\u8ca0\u9762\u66f8\u5beb\uff1a\u6587\u5316\u7b26\u865f\u7684\u5fb5\u72c0\u5f0f\u95b1\u8b80 | ISBN = 9578453922 | accessdate = 2020-03-30 | url = https://www.books.com.tw/products/0010109140 | language = Traditional Chinese }} </ref>\n* ''Eight Essays on Literature and the Other Arts: Intertextuality, Counterpoint and Cultural Interpretation''.  Taipei: San Ming Books Publisher. 193ps. (with review system) <ref> {{Cite book | author = \u5289\u7d00\u8559 | title = \u6587\u5b78\u8207\u85dd\u8853\u516b\u8ad6\uff1a\u4e92\u6587\u2027\u5c0d\u4f4d\u2027\u6587\u5316\u8a6e\u91cb| ISBN = 9789571421 | accessdate = 2020-03-30 | url = https://www.books.com.tw/products/0010376850?sloc=main | language = Traditional Chinese }} </ref>\n\n=== Co-edited volumes ===\n* ''Inter-Asia Cultural Studies. Special Issue: Artistic mediation of Decolonized Body.'' Eds. Joyce C.H. Liu & Naoki Sakai. Vol. 19, Issue 4 (Dec. 2018). <ref> {{Cite book | author = Joyce C.H. Liu & Naoki Sakai | title = Inter-Asia Cultural Studies. Special Issue: Artistic mediation of Decolonized Body | accessdate = 2020-03-30 | url = https://www.tandfonline.com/toc/riac20/19/4?nav=tocList | language = English  }} </ref>\n* ''The Position of Philosophy and Politics: Special Issue on Alain Badiou.'' Chung Wai Literary Quarterly. Vol. 47, No. 3. September 2018.\n* ''East-Asian Marxisms and their Trajectories.'' Eds. Joyce C.H. Liu & Viren Mirthy. London: Routledge, 2017. <ref> {{Cite book | author = Joyce C.H. Liu, Viren Murthy | title = East-Asian Marxisms and Their Trajectories | publisher = Routledge | date = 2017-02-03 | ISBN = 9781315687582 | accessdate = 2020-03-30 | url = https://www.routledge.com/East-Asian-Marxisms-and-Their-Trajectories-1st-Edition/Liu-Murthy/p/book/9781138919846 | language = English }} </ref>\n* ''European-East Asian Borders in Translation''. Eds. Joyce C. H. Liu and Nick Vaughan-Williams. London: Routledge, 2013. Forthcoming. <ref> {{Cite book | author = Joyce C.H. Liu, Nick Vaughan-Williams | title = European-East Asian Borders in Translation | publisher = Routledge | date = 2014-08-21 | ISBN = 9780203746660 | accessdate = 2020-03-30 | url = https://www.routledge.com/European-East-Asian-Borders-in-Translation/CH-Liu-Vaughan-Williams/p/book/9780415831314 | language = English  }} </ref>\n* ''Biopolitics, Ethics and Subjectivation.'' Eds. Joyce C.H. Liu & Alain Brossai, Yuan-Horng Chu, Rada Ivekovic. Paris: L\u2019Harmattan, 2011. <ref> {{Cite book | author =  Alain Brossat, Yuan-Horng Chu, Rada Ivekovi\u0107, Joyce C.H. Liu | title = Biopolitics, Ethics and Subjectivation | publisher = L'Harmattan | date = 2011-03-09 | ISBN = 9782296545458 | accessdate = 2020-03-30 | url = https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/28261697-biopolitics-ethics-and-subjectivation | language = English }} </ref>\n* ''Special Issue: Koyasu Nobukuni'' Joyce C.H. Liu. Ed. Router: A Journal of Cultural Studies. 2008.\n* ''Visual Culture and Critical Theory I: Empire, Asia and the Question of Subject'' Ed. Joyce Chi-Hui Liu. Taipei: Ryefield Publisher, 2006. <ref> {{Cite book | author = \u5289\u7d00\u8559 | title = \u6587\u5316\u7684\u8996\u89ba\u7cfb\u7d71\u2160\uff1a\u5e1d\u570b\u2500\u4e9e\u6d32\u2500\u4e3b\u9ad4\u6027 | location = Taiwan | publisher = \u9ea5\u7530 | date = 2006-09-16 | ISBN = 9861730907 | accessdate = 2020-03-30 | url = https://www.books.com.tw/products/0010342134 | language = Traditional Chinese }} </ref>\n* ''Visual Culture and Critical Theory II: Everyday Life and Popular Culture'' Ed. Joyce Chi-Hui Liu. Taipei: Ryefield Publisher, 2006. <ref> {{Cite book | author = \u5289\u7d00\u8559 | title = \u6587\u5316\u7684\u8996\u89ba\u7cfb\u7d71\u2161\uff1a\u65e5\u5e38\u751f\u6d3b\u8207\u5927\u773e\u6587\u5316 | location = Taiwan | publisher = \u9ea5\u7530 | date = 2006-09-16 |  ISBN = 9861730915 | accessdate = 2